    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI currently utilize two languages — English and Romanian — while having the `spelloptions = \"camel\"` setting enabled in my config.\r\n\r\nNevertheless, a recurring source of frustration arises when I open any file, only to find that the spellcheck verification is inactive. This compels me to input `:set spelloptions=camel` manually each time I wish to activate the spellchecker.\r\n\r\nAfter some time, i found what `noplainbuffer` is appended when treesitter is trriggered: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/72e619ca92b527140e1323f4e281b7f3ad35f380/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/highlighter.lua#L134\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>How it looks now</summary>\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/22500212/84f1848e-7820-4368-a3fe-02c2a8ae7b63)\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/assets/22500212/22a0fa21-efd2-481a-a528-8cc7d9d77960)\r\n </details>\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>How i expect to be</summary>\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/22500212/65b03b51-601d-4111-99fe-0b3cc7179837)\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/22500212/e2d6fc82-3ad4-48cd-aa85-71c8dd950abb)\r\n </details>\r\n\r\nNeovim options:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal options = {\r\n  relativenumber = true,\r\n  spell = true,\r\n  spelllang = \"en_us,ro\",\r\n  spelloptions = \"camel\",\r\n}\r\n\r\nfor k, v in pairs(options) do\r\n  vim.opt[k] = v\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Test code</summary>\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconsole.log(\"Aplle\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Bananna\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Caffine\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Diamound\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Elixer\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Febuary\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Gravvy\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Habbit\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Incorect\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Jurney\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Kitchin\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Latttuce\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Mischevious\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Nise\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Occured\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Pannini\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Qeustion\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Relevent\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Seperete\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Truely\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Unkown\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Vaccum\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Wendsday\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Xceitement\");\r\nconsole.log(\"Yerning\");\r\n\r\nconsole.log('applePie')\r\nconsole.log('BananaSplit')\r\nconsole.log('ChocolateCake')\r\nconsole.log('dougnutHole')\r\nconsole.log('ElephantEars')\r\nconsole.log('Frappucino')\r\nconsole.log('GrapfruiteJuice')\r\nconsole.log('HamburgrHelper')\r\nconsole.log('iceCreem')\r\nconsole.log('JalepenoPopper')\r\nconsole.log('KeyLimePie')\r\nconsole.log('LemonMerrinque')\r\nconsole.log('Marshmellow')\r\nconsole.log('NoodleSopp')\r\nconsole.log('OnionRings')\r\nconsole.log('PanniniPress')\r\nconsole.log('Quessadilla')\r\nconsole.log('Raspberrry')\r\nconsole.log('StrawberrieShortcake')\r\nconsole.log('Tiramisu')\r\nconsole.log('UnicorneCake')\r\nconsole.log('VanillaBean')\r\nconsole.log('WaffleCone')\r\nconsole.log('XtraFudge')\r\nconsole.log('Yogourt')\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nOption `noplainbuffer` should not block spellcheck verification, even if `camel` is enabled or `noplainbuffer` should not be added to `spelloptions` if `camel` option already exists",
